window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Brought to you by Penguin.</b></p> <p><b>This audiobook in The Thursday Murder Club series is read by a new narrator, Fiona Shaw.</b></p> <p><b>A new mystery is afoot in the third book in the Thursday Murder Club series from record-breaking, bestselling author Richard Osman.</b></p> <p><b>This audiobook includes an exclusive interview between Richard Osman and journalist and TV presenter Steph McGovern.</b></p> <p>It is an ordinary Thursday, and things should finally be returning to normal.</p> <p>Except trouble is never far away where the Thursday Murder Club are concerned. A local news legend is on the hunt for a sensational headline, and soon the gang are hot on the trail of two murders, ten years apart.</p> <p>To make matters worse, a new nemesis pays Elizabeth a visit, presenting her with a deadly mission: kill or be killed...</p> <p>While Elizabeth grapples with her conscience (and a gun), the gang and their unlikely new friends (including TV stars, money launderers and ex-KGB colonels) unravel a new mystery. But can they catch the culprit and save Elizabeth before the murderer strikes again?</p>"; 
